node.text:
I love and accept myself exactly as I am.

Say it with us. Say it out loud. Speak to your heart.

I love and accept myself exactly as I am.

Right now.

Exactly as I am.

With flaws. Fears. What sometimes feels like brokenness and unworthiness.

I love myself. I accept all of me.

I see all of me. I accept me. There is nowhere else, no one else, that I need to be.

There is no more perfect space, time, energy, then right now. 

So let’s start with now.

Not once we achieve that thing. Earn that amount. Create that creation. Meet that goal.

Right now.

Not for the sake of forward movement.

But for the sake of our hearts, our Souls, we who have been through so much.

We deserve that love right now.

We deserve to be witnessed exactly as we are.

Not later.

Not once we have ‘proven’ ourselves worthy somehow.

We were always worthy.

You were always worthy.

You right now, are worthy.

It doesn't matter how you are spending your time. It doesn't matter what you were taught to believe about yourself.

The mistakes you have made don't matter. Or the fears that sometimes drive your actions.

It doesn't matter what you have achieved or not achieved,  what you look like, your weight or your skin.

It doesn't matter. It is irrelevant.

But your worth. The light that is inside of you. Your heart. The very fabric of who you are...

It is unquestionably worthy of being loved and accepted right now.

It is non-negotiable.

And whenever you feel that voice piping in with all the reasons why you aren’t.

Remember…

It’s non-negotiable.

Simple as that.

...sorry voice.

♡
